27/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Armed Forces and the US Army will hold a joint military exercise at the Mahovljani Airport near Banja Luka on August 2nd, the news agency Fena said Thursday (July 26th).The drill aims to boost military co-operation, and will focus on preparing to participate in peacekeeping missions.
Several BiH commanders will be presented with certificates for their contribution to the BiH's participation in the peacekeeping activates in Iraq, and the BiH Armed Forces will given special military equipment.
(Fena - 26/07/07)
